  "text": "According to Mansini et al. [CITATION_1] , there are two types of models in portfolio optimization problems that have real futures, namely relative and absolute. If a model has decision variables in shares or percentages, the model is called the relative model and the variables relative. However, a model may have real futures in absolute values as well. In this case, the model is called the absolute model and the variables absolute.",
